pageContext.claim: “The only way, by the way -- and the only way they get in is by going around it; they're not going over it because you have a lot of tremendous people watching. They can't get the ladders and go over it. Plus, it's very dangerous. It's very high to go over it. So when Gloria says [assaults have dropped] "65 percent," this is 100 percent, but when they go down further.”
pageContext.analysis: Customs and Border Protection only reports assaults against law enforcement personnel by Fiscal Year not by location. The Fact Checker asked for additional information, but they were not able to provide a more detailed breakdown of data.
